1
00:00:22,580 --> 00:00:27,660
♪Don't be afraid of the long journey♪

2
00:00:29,780 --> 00:00:34,740
♪Love will comfort your missing♪

3
00:00:34,900 --> 00:00:38,620
♪All the wounds will scab over♪

4
00:00:38,740 --> 00:00:41,980
♪And turn into the blossoms of time♪

5
00:00:41,980 --> 00:00:48,700
♪Someone will wipe them away for you♪

6
00:00:49,300 --> 00:00:52,580
♪Don't feel lonely, moving on♪

7
00:00:52,940 --> 00:00:56,420
♪Share your story with time♪

8
00:00:56,460 --> 00:01:03,100
♪It will respond
with a gentle beam of light♪

9
00:01:03,220 --> 00:01:06,820
♪Wishing you find her in the crowd♪

10
00:01:07,100 --> 00:01:10,220
♪And rest content with a simple life♪

11
00:01:10,380 --> 00:01:16,660
♪Even though life is full of regrets♪

12
00:01:17,380 --> 00:01:20,180
♪May you always maintain enthusiasm♪

13
00:01:20,220 --> 00:01:22,540
♪For every winter and summer♪

14
00:01:23,900 --> 00:01:25,980
[Love Is Panacea]
[Episode 2]

15
00:01:25,980 --> 00:01:26,960
[The show is the Major Project
for Supporting Literature and Art]

16
00:01:26,960 --> 00:01:27,980
[in Sichuan Province in 2022]

17
00:01:27,980 --> 00:01:29,980
[Based on the novel "Healer"
by Ningmeng Yuyan]

18
00:01:30,160 --> 00:01:31,760
What could be better for you

19
00:01:31,760 --> 00:01:32,560
than this French interpreter job?

20
00:01:32,880 --> 00:01:33,760
No way.

21
00:01:42,960 --> 00:01:44,280
I haven't tried it yet.

22
00:01:44,280 --> 00:01:45,680
Why do you say I can't do it?

23
00:01:48,280 --> 00:01:49,560
Yes, Dr. Gu.

24
00:01:49,720 --> 00:01:50,680
Wei'an can do it.

25
00:01:51,040 --> 00:01:52,080
She's very good at French.

26
00:01:52,280 --> 00:01:53,280
And she knows medicine.

27
00:01:53,760 --> 00:01:54,760
She even saved someone today,

28
00:01:54,760 --> 00:01:55,680
didn't you know?

29
00:01:55,680 --> 00:01:56,400
You even helped us.

30
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:59,080
So you're the surgical genius.

31
00:01:59,560 --> 00:02:00,400
That hole,

32
00:02:00,400 --> 00:02:01,680
you aimed it perfectly.

33
00:02:08,320 --> 00:02:10,910
Working at a hospital is hard
and poorly paid.

34
00:02:11,120 --> 00:02:11,920
You can't keep it up.

35
00:02:12,520 --> 00:02:13,320
It's not suitable.

36
00:02:15,640 --> 00:02:17,600
Can I apply for the job?

37
00:02:17,760 --> 00:02:18,640
I know French, too.

38
00:02:21,040 --> 00:02:22,320
Subarachnoid hemorrhage.

39
00:02:23,080 --> 00:02:24,320
Spinal cord injury classification.

40
00:02:24,960 --> 00:02:26,040
Cranial nerve palsy.

41
00:02:26,640 --> 00:02:27,600
Translate, please.

42
00:02:30,120 --> 00:02:31,720
(I don't even know
what they mean in Chinese.)

43
00:02:31,760 --> 00:02:32,960
(Not to mention French.)

44
00:02:34,640 --> 00:02:35,560
I...

45
00:02:42,120 --> 00:02:43,760
I...

46
00:02:45,560 --> 00:02:47,560
But I have a heart to dedicate.

47
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:49,760
I want to do my little part.

48
00:02:56,560 --> 00:02:57,560
Well, your little part

49
00:02:57,840 --> 00:02:59,640
seems insignificant enough to ignore.

50
00:03:00,560 --> 00:03:01,280
Forget it.

51
00:03:01,640 --> 00:03:03,280
We just want to pay you back
as soon as possible,

52
00:03:03,280 --> 00:03:03,840
Dr. Gu.

53
00:03:03,920 --> 00:03:04,360
No need to repay it.

54
00:03:04,640 --> 00:03:05,120
No way!

55
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:07,560
Debts should be repaid.

56
00:03:10,200 --> 00:03:11,240
Boss.

57
00:03:11,360 --> 00:03:14,000
It's the first time I've seen someone
with debts act so boldly.

58
00:03:17,280 --> 00:03:18,760
Dr. Gu.

59
00:03:21,760 --> 00:03:22,680
The patient has

60
00:03:22,680 --> 00:03:26,360
grade 5 muscle strength in the
left upper limb and both lower limbs.

61
00:03:26,360 --> 00:03:28,840
The neck is soft with no stiff-neck.

62
00:03:28,840 --> 00:03:30,280
The Babinski sign is negative.

63
00:03:30,400 --> 00:03:31,840
The patient is recovering well.

64
00:03:32,280 --> 00:03:32,880
Pardon.

65
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:33,960
Grade 5 muscle strength...

66
00:03:34,080 --> 00:03:35,800
Grade 5 muscle strength

67
00:03:35,960 --> 00:03:36,680
in the left upper limb
and both lower limbs.

68
00:03:36,920 --> 00:03:38,440
The neck is soft with no stiff-neck.

69
00:03:38,680 --> 00:03:39,920
The Babinski sign is negative.

70
00:03:39,920 --> 00:03:41,160
The patient's condition is normal.

71
00:03:41,480 --> 00:03:42,440
He's recovering well.

72
00:03:45,800 --> 00:03:47,480
Is this our new interpreter?

73
00:03:48,640 --> 00:03:50,640
See, I told you Wei'an can do it.

74
00:03:52,120 --> 00:03:53,080
That's right, boss.

75
00:03:53,080 --> 00:03:53,920
She's amazing.

76
00:03:54,680 --> 00:03:56,320
We've got a powerful interpreter.

77
00:03:59,520 --> 00:04:00,320
Thank you.

78
00:04:00,480 --> 00:04:01,520
You're welcome.

79
00:04:04,640 --> 00:04:05,640
You have a one-month probation period.

80
00:04:06,320 --> 00:04:07,960
I hope you won't give up halfway.

81
00:04:10,040 --> 00:04:10,960
Hold on.

82
00:04:13,320 --> 00:04:14,320
Is there anything else to discuss?

83
00:04:15,040 --> 00:04:16,320
Let's clarify the conditions first.

84
00:04:17,070 --> 00:04:19,320
Weekly pay, full board.

85
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:22,320
Also, Jiang Muying must join me
in starting the job.

86
00:04:22,600 --> 00:04:24,320
And we're moving in tonight.

87
00:04:24,960 --> 00:04:26,760
We only need one interpreter.

88
00:04:30,480 --> 00:04:31,480
The more, the merrier.

89
00:04:31,480 --> 00:04:32,320
Boss.

90
00:04:32,640 --> 00:04:33,960
But professional French vocabulary...

91
00:04:33,960 --> 00:04:34,440
She can learn.

92
00:04:34,440 --> 00:04:35,080
- I can learn.
- I can teach.

93
00:04:42,920 --> 00:04:44,320
Arrange dormitories for both of them.

94
00:04:47,320 --> 00:04:49,440
Wei'an, you were amazing just now.

95
00:04:49,680 --> 00:04:51,640
You translated

96
00:04:51,640 --> 00:04:52,920
such a long list of medical terms.

97
00:04:53,760 --> 00:04:55,640
It shows that even though you dropped
out of school for three years,

98
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:58,160
you haven't forgotten your expertise.

99
00:04:58,760 --> 00:05:01,600
This knowledge has been ingrained
in your bones

100
00:05:01,960 --> 00:05:03,080
and your instincts.

101
00:05:05,880 --> 00:05:06,640
Not really...

102
00:05:09,760 --> 00:05:10,480
Wait.

103
00:05:11,040 --> 00:05:12,320
It's only been a while.

104
00:05:13,320 --> 00:05:14,320
Where did you get the clothes?

105
00:05:14,760 --> 00:05:15,760
Clothes? You remind me.

106
00:05:16,320 --> 00:05:17,760
All my beautiful clothes in the suitcase

107
00:05:17,760 --> 00:05:18,800
were all gone.

108
00:05:19,040 --> 00:05:20,760
If I hadn't found a night market nearby,

109
00:05:20,760 --> 00:05:21,880
I wouldn't have any clothes
to change tomorrow.

110
00:05:23,760 --> 00:05:25,200
I've bought some for you too.

111
00:05:25,520 --> 00:05:26,320
Take a look.

112
00:05:27,320 --> 00:05:28,320
Do you want to change?

113
00:05:32,160 --> 00:05:33,160
Let's put them away.

114
00:05:34,520 --> 00:05:35,320
Alright.

115
00:05:41,080 --> 00:05:43,440
Is this left by the previous doctor?

116
00:05:43,800 --> 00:05:45,440
If you hadn't dropped out of school,

117
00:05:45,440 --> 00:05:46,880
you'd probably be a resident by now.

118
00:05:46,880 --> 00:05:48,400
I'm sure you'd be wearing this lab coat.

119
00:05:48,400 --> 00:05:49,320
How cool it would be!

120
00:05:54,800 --> 00:05:56,920
I'll put this in the cabinet.

121
00:05:56,920 --> 00:05:57,920
You can try it later.

122
00:06:07,060 --> 00:06:10,700
[China Trade Corporation in Lacaya]

123
00:06:17,520 --> 00:06:18,560
These guys are awesome.

124
00:06:19,440 --> 00:06:21,200
They've been here
for hours without moving,

125
00:06:21,440 --> 00:06:22,520
not even going to the restroom.

126
00:06:24,560 --> 00:06:26,200
Maybe we should come back another day.

127
00:06:26,200 --> 00:06:27,160
No.

128
00:06:27,520 --> 00:06:29,200
My hard-earned money is inside.

129
00:06:31,200 --> 00:06:31,760
No way.

130
00:06:31,760 --> 00:06:32,960
We have to do something.

131
00:06:51,640 --> 00:06:52,880
Make money!

132
00:06:55,760 --> 00:06:56,680
Who is he?

133
00:06:57,120 --> 00:06:57,880
My employee.

134
00:06:58,080 --> 00:06:59,200
I miss you so much, Mommy An!

135
00:06:59,360 --> 00:07:00,000
Okay.

136
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:00,680
Don't speak anymore.

137
00:07:00,960 --> 00:07:02,400
I'm busy right now.

138
00:07:12,200 --> 00:07:13,880
Sakun!

139
00:07:16,280 --> 00:07:16,960
It's dangerous.

140
00:07:17,200 --> 00:07:18,200
Sakun!

141
00:07:18,760 --> 00:07:19,790
Wait, Su Wei'an.

142
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:21,080
You hired a child?

143
00:07:21,320 --> 00:07:22,200
No.

144
00:07:22,790 --> 00:07:24,240
He just runs errands for me.

145
00:07:24,430 --> 00:07:25,640
Like delivering milk to customers.

146
00:07:26,520 --> 00:07:27,400
Sakun!

147
00:07:28,200 --> 00:07:29,550
He just called you mommy.

148
00:07:29,760 --> 00:07:31,760
He calls anyone who's nice to him
mommy and daddy.

149
00:07:34,560 --> 00:07:35,760
He has several siblings in his family.

150
00:07:37,200 --> 00:07:38,680
And Sakun has been sick since birth.

151
00:07:39,640 --> 00:07:40,680
His mother doesn't care about him.

152
00:07:41,760 --> 00:07:44,200
And his dad has passed away.

153
00:07:46,520 --> 00:07:47,560
What illness?

154
00:07:49,680 --> 00:07:50,480
AIDS.

155
00:07:53,080 --> 00:07:53,800
Sakun!

156
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:00,960
How do you know it?

157
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:03,320
I always knew it meant a lot to you.

158
00:08:06,200 --> 00:08:06,880
Let's go!

159
00:08:12,360 --> 00:08:13,200
Sakun.

160
00:08:14,200 --> 00:08:15,400
Have you been good lately?

161
00:08:15,760 --> 00:08:17,120
Remember what I told you?

162
00:08:17,200 --> 00:08:19,200
Don't get hurt or bleed.

163
00:08:19,240 --> 00:08:20,440
Did you take your medicine on time?

164
00:08:20,520 --> 00:08:23,280
No, Mom can't afford it.

165
00:08:25,680 --> 00:08:26,880
Do you feel any discomfort anywhere?

166
00:08:26,960 --> 00:08:28,400
Headache.

167
00:08:29,800 --> 00:08:31,560
Why don't you go to the hospital?

168
00:08:31,640 --> 00:08:33,720
Mom says it's too expensive.
We can't afford it.

169
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:37,200
It's okay, Sakun.

170
00:08:38,200 --> 00:08:39,000
We'll make money.

171
00:08:39,200 --> 00:08:40,200
Great! Make money!

172
00:08:40,360 --> 00:08:42,240
Sakun!

173
00:08:42,240 --> 00:08:43,320
Where are you?

174
00:08:43,440 --> 00:08:44,200
Mom.

175
00:08:46,200 --> 00:08:46,800
Be careful!

176
00:08:47,560 --> 00:08:48,560
Where did you go?

177
00:08:49,680 --> 00:08:50,440
Where have you been?

178
00:08:51,120 --> 00:08:53,240
Who told you to run around?

179
00:08:53,320 --> 00:08:54,200
Go home!

180
00:08:55,960 --> 00:08:57,280
Mom, I've got a headache.

181
00:08:57,320 --> 00:08:58,080
If you go to sleep,

182
00:08:58,080 --> 00:08:59,680
you won't feel the headache anymore.

183
00:09:01,800 --> 00:09:02,920
Have you seen An?

184
00:09:04,680 --> 00:09:05,440
No, I haven't.

185
00:09:06,040 --> 00:09:08,040
Tell mom if you see her.

186
00:09:08,120 --> 00:09:11,160
It's bad luck to rent to her.

187
00:09:11,160 --> 00:09:13,280
The house is damaged so badly.

188
00:09:13,280 --> 00:09:14,520
She should compensate us
with a large sum of money.

189
00:09:14,520 --> 00:09:15,880
A large sum of money!

190
00:09:15,880 --> 00:09:17,240
I must find her!

191
00:09:17,520 --> 00:09:18,440
What are you doing?

192
00:09:18,560 --> 00:09:19,760
You'll have to pay for it
if you go out now.

193
00:09:19,760 --> 00:09:20,560
I'm going to compensate her.

194
00:09:20,680 --> 00:09:21,320
For Sakun's treatment.

195
00:09:22,440 --> 00:09:23,200
Are you crazy?

196
00:09:24,160 --> 00:09:24,960
You work so hard to earn money

197
00:09:24,960 --> 00:09:27,040
just to treat a child
who's not even related to you?

198
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:28,200
Are you nuts?

199
00:09:28,320 --> 00:09:29,560
His mother doesn't even care about him.

200
00:09:29,560 --> 00:09:30,440
Why do you take care of him?

201
00:09:32,720 --> 00:09:33,920
Because we share the same fate.

202
00:09:34,960 --> 00:09:36,200
What nonsense!

203
00:09:38,440 --> 00:09:40,280
Wake up, Su Wei'an!

204
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:42,960
AIDS is incurable.

205
00:09:42,960 --> 00:09:43,600
You know that.

206
00:09:44,600 --> 00:09:45,600
What about him?

207
00:09:46,200 --> 00:09:47,200
Should he just wait to die?

208
00:09:49,440 --> 00:09:50,200
He's still so young.

209
00:09:50,560 --> 00:09:51,960
As long as he takes his medicine

210
00:09:52,200 --> 00:09:52,920
and controls his condition well,

211
00:09:52,920 --> 00:09:54,200
he'll be cured one day.

212
00:09:55,600 --> 00:09:56,800
Wait! What's wrong with you?

213
00:09:59,440 --> 00:10:00,440
I mean,

214
00:10:00,680 --> 00:10:02,040
even if you pay him money,

215
00:10:02,160 --> 00:10:03,680
will his mother take him to a doctor?

216
00:10:06,480 --> 00:10:07,200
Yeah, you're right.

217
00:10:10,200 --> 00:10:12,200
It's not just money.
He needs medicine more than anything.

218
00:10:19,220 --> 00:10:22,220
[Friendship Hospital]

219
00:10:25,840 --> 00:10:26,440
Dr. Gu.

220
00:10:27,800 --> 00:10:28,440
Are you okay, Wei'an?

221
00:10:28,440 --> 00:10:29,200
I'm fine.

222
00:10:38,200 --> 00:10:39,200
You've dropped out of school.

223
00:10:39,600 --> 00:10:41,440
Why do you still keep your campus card
from Huaren Medical University?

224
00:10:42,920 --> 00:10:44,680
Why don't you throw it away

225
00:10:44,680 --> 00:10:45,400
along with your dream?

226
00:10:45,600 --> 00:10:46,440
Why should I throw it away?

227
00:10:47,200 --> 00:10:48,280
There's still money in it.

228
00:10:48,280 --> 00:10:49,400
I can use it when I go back to school.

229
00:11:04,800 --> 00:11:06,600
I folded it up and put it in the box.

230
00:11:06,600 --> 00:11:07,200
Okay.

231
00:11:12,660 --> 00:11:14,980
[Jinhai People's Insurance Company
Personal Accident Insurance Policy]

232
00:11:16,720 --> 00:11:17,400
Wei'an.

233
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:19,880
Why did you buy such a large amount
of accident insurance?

234
00:11:20,680 --> 00:11:22,680
[Beneficiary: Zhao Meilan]
And the beneficiary is your mom?

235
00:11:24,820 --> 00:11:27,200
It's not a good thing
to buy an accident insurance.

236
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:28,680
Why do you curse yourself?

237
00:11:30,200 --> 00:11:31,800
Fortunes can change in an instant.

238
00:11:32,320 --> 00:11:33,960
I'm alone in a foreign country.

239
00:11:34,200 --> 00:11:36,200
Who knows what might happen?

240
00:11:37,800 --> 00:11:38,560
And you,

241
00:11:39,200 --> 00:11:40,720
if you insist on following me,

242
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:42,200
I suggest you get one too.

243
00:11:42,280 --> 00:11:43,000
Bah...

244
00:11:43,080 --> 00:11:44,160
Don't curse me!

245
00:11:44,440 --> 00:11:45,400
I'm not cursing you.

246
00:11:49,460 --> 00:11:51,700
[Zhao Meilan's Moments]

247
00:11:57,040 --> 00:11:57,800
What are you looking at?

248
00:11:59,800 --> 00:12:00,640
Let me show you.

249
00:12:02,560 --> 00:12:03,920
She's gone square dancing again.

250
00:12:07,080 --> 00:12:08,200
Lan is so cute.

251
00:12:16,200 --> 00:12:17,200
Jiang.

252
00:12:17,600 --> 00:12:20,200
You've been in Lacaya for long enough.

253
00:12:20,680 --> 00:12:21,600
Why don't you go home early?

254
00:12:23,080 --> 00:12:24,200
I'm really busy here.

255
00:12:25,680 --> 00:12:27,200
Tell Lan when you get back

256
00:12:27,440 --> 00:12:30,200
that I'm doing well in Paris.

257
00:12:30,480 --> 00:12:31,560
Are you kidding me?

258
00:12:31,720 --> 00:12:33,720
It's so different from Paris.

259
00:12:35,560 --> 00:12:36,560
Not so bad.

260
00:12:37,200 --> 00:12:39,840
Working in the city center
and living in a double room.

261
00:12:40,200 --> 00:12:42,200
The healthcare
and catering are well-matched.

262
00:12:43,200 --> 00:12:44,200
What's wrong with it?

263
00:12:49,080 --> 00:12:49,680
Alright.

264
00:12:50,680 --> 00:12:52,200
Since it's so good here,
I won't leave then.

265
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:56,200
I, Jiang Muying, have a job now.

266
00:12:56,560 --> 00:12:57,560
I'm also an interpreter.

267
00:13:03,560 --> 00:13:04,200
Okay.

268
00:13:06,200 --> 00:13:07,760
Go to bed. It's late.

269
00:13:09,200 --> 00:13:09,920
What about you?

270
00:13:10,800 --> 00:13:11,560
I'll go to sleep soon.

271
00:13:12,280 --> 00:13:12,840
Okay.

272
00:13:20,400 --> 00:13:21,080
Wei'an.

273
00:13:22,320 --> 00:13:24,160
I feel like you've changed a lot

274
00:13:24,160 --> 00:13:25,800
in the three years
since we last saw each other.

275
00:13:36,140 --> 00:13:38,620
[Zhao Meilan's Moments]

276
00:13:41,700 --> 00:13:46,500
[Friendship Hospital]

277
00:14:04,200 --> 00:14:05,080
Oh, honey.

278
00:14:05,400 --> 00:14:06,600
I'm still at the office.

279
00:14:08,680 --> 00:14:10,040
I don't have any plans for tomorrow.

280
00:14:10,040 --> 00:14:11,040
How about you?

281
00:14:14,200 --> 00:14:16,200
It looks like it's going
to rain heavily outside.

282
00:14:19,200 --> 00:14:20,200
Okay.

283
00:14:21,200 --> 00:14:23,680
The signal here is not good
when it rains.

284
00:14:28,040 --> 00:14:29,240
I'm going out to talk to you.

285
00:14:32,640 --> 00:14:34,960
Why don't you come pick me up?

286
00:14:35,640 --> 00:14:38,240
I don't think I'm going to make it
to your place today.

287
00:14:39,160 --> 00:14:40,080
Okay.

288
00:14:54,080 --> 00:14:54,920
Hi, Security.

289
00:14:55,680 --> 00:14:56,520
There was someone...

290
00:14:56,640 --> 00:14:57,480
(If the security guards catch her,)

291
00:14:57,560 --> 00:14:59,160
(she would be retaken
to the police station.)

292
00:14:59,360 --> 00:15:00,240
It's okay.

293
00:15:02,200 --> 00:15:04,080
But why don't you come pick me up?

294
00:15:04,080 --> 00:15:05,920
I want to come to you.

295
00:15:08,200 --> 00:15:10,440
Yes, I miss you too.

296
00:15:12,200 --> 00:15:15,200
You can come to the hospital
to pick me up.

297
00:15:23,520 --> 00:15:24,760
What are you doing?

298
00:15:30,440 --> 00:15:31,560
Okay, I love you.

299
00:15:34,480 --> 00:15:35,440
Bye.

300
00:16:16,480 --> 00:16:17,560
Su Wei'an.

301
00:16:18,960 --> 00:16:20,200
What are you doing here?

302
00:16:21,080 --> 00:16:22,360
Don't you know
that trespassing in the pharmacy

303
00:16:22,360 --> 00:16:23,480
can be a crime?

304
00:16:24,200 --> 00:16:25,760
No, I didn't trespass.

305
00:16:25,760 --> 00:16:26,320
I...

306
00:16:26,680 --> 00:16:27,960
I'm here to see...

307
00:16:39,680 --> 00:16:40,440
Atazanavir,

308
00:16:42,200 --> 00:16:43,520
the medicine for AIDS.

309
00:16:44,480 --> 00:16:45,200
You tried

310
00:16:45,680 --> 00:16:46,320
to steal the medicine?

311
00:16:46,600 --> 00:16:47,960
Of course not.

312
00:16:48,560 --> 00:16:49,560
Don't say it like that.

313
00:16:56,600 --> 00:16:57,440
I'm here to buy the medicine.

314
00:17:01,560 --> 00:17:02,560
Stop denying!

315
00:17:05,080 --> 00:17:06,320
Now, I have reason to suspect

316
00:17:06,600 --> 00:17:08,200
that you're selling
prescription drugs illegally.

317
00:17:09,320 --> 00:17:10,320
No wonder

318
00:17:11,440 --> 00:17:14,200
you suddenly came to the hospital
to apply for an interpreter job.

319
00:17:14,480 --> 00:17:16,200
So this was your plan.

320
00:17:17,200 --> 00:17:17,880
Don't talk that way.

321
00:17:19,280 --> 00:17:19,880
Dr. Gu.

322
00:17:20,160 --> 00:17:21,600
Dr. Gu, please listen to me.

323
00:17:22,440 --> 00:17:23,200
Dr. Gu.

324
00:17:24,720 --> 00:17:26,000
Security!

325
00:17:26,400 --> 00:17:27,120
Is anyone there?

326
00:17:27,120 --> 00:17:27,760
Be quiet.

327
00:17:27,920 --> 00:17:28,680
Hello?

328
00:17:30,200 --> 00:17:31,200
We'll be caught.

329
00:17:31,400 --> 00:17:32,200
You've got a lot of guts.

330
00:17:33,040 --> 00:17:34,200
You're still afraid of being found?

331
00:17:35,680 --> 00:17:36,520
When I saw you acting suspiciously

332
00:17:36,520 --> 00:17:37,960
outside just now,

333
00:17:37,960 --> 00:17:39,640
I should have called security
to take you away.

334
00:17:39,840 --> 00:17:41,280
And we wouldn't be locked up here now.

335
00:17:41,680 --> 00:17:42,680
Let me explain.

336
00:17:46,600 --> 00:17:47,440
What are you doing?

337
00:17:47,640 --> 00:17:48,920
Calling security.

338
00:17:49,840 --> 00:17:51,760
No, please don't.

339
00:17:58,960 --> 00:17:59,960
I forgot to tell you.

340
00:18:00,200 --> 00:18:02,200
The base station is unstable here
when it rains.

341
00:18:02,960 --> 00:18:03,720
No signal.

342
00:18:06,760 --> 00:18:07,840
It seems like fate.

343
00:18:10,200 --> 00:18:10,960
I guess

344
00:18:10,960 --> 00:18:13,200
you won't take me
to the police station again, will you?

345
00:18:19,960 --> 00:18:20,960
Don't you know

346
00:18:22,680 --> 00:18:23,680
that the main switch controls

347
00:18:25,200 --> 00:18:27,200
the lights in the pharmacy?

348
00:18:41,440 --> 00:18:42,440
What are you planning to do now?

349
00:18:43,360 --> 00:18:45,200
Find something to break the window.

350
00:18:45,880 --> 00:18:46,920
No!

351
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:48,640
We'll be discovered if you do that.

352
00:18:49,960 --> 00:18:51,080
What do you mean by "we"?

353
00:18:51,440 --> 00:18:52,640
What's it got to do with me?

354
00:18:54,120 --> 00:18:55,600
You dared to come here
to steal medicine.

355
00:18:56,000 --> 00:18:57,720
You should have thought
about the consequences.

356
00:18:58,720 --> 00:18:59,200
No, I didn't.

357
00:19:04,480 --> 00:19:05,200
Fine.

358
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:06,680
Go ahead.

359
00:19:07,360 --> 00:19:08,680
You recruited me anyway.

360
00:19:09,040 --> 00:19:10,400
If we get caught,

361
00:19:10,640 --> 00:19:11,800
I'll say

362
00:19:11,800 --> 00:19:13,600
that you ordered me to steal

363
00:19:14,360 --> 00:19:15,200
and sell the medication.

364
00:19:15,480 --> 00:19:16,680
We'll split the profit 70/30.

365
00:19:16,960 --> 00:19:18,200
Seven for you, three for me.

366
00:19:21,920 --> 00:19:22,600
Wait.

367
00:19:23,680 --> 00:19:26,200
Don't you have any morals?

368
00:19:26,640 --> 00:19:27,440
What's that?

369
00:19:28,480 --> 00:19:28,960
Is it worth anything?

370
00:19:43,240 --> 00:19:44,000
Ah! Snake!

371
00:19:44,120 --> 00:19:45,200
Get your hands off me!

372
00:19:45,960 --> 00:19:47,440
It's just a gecko.

373
00:19:59,200 --> 00:20:01,920
It was a birthday gift from my mother.

374
00:20:02,000 --> 00:20:03,480
What's the big deal?

375
00:20:03,680 --> 00:20:05,040
I just wanted to take a look.

376
00:20:10,600 --> 00:20:11,760
I'm sorry. I didn't mean to.

377
00:20:11,760 --> 00:20:12,600
I'm really sorry.

378
00:20:16,200 --> 00:20:17,370
Please don't be angry.

379
00:20:17,400 --> 00:20:18,320
I was just

380
00:20:18,480 --> 00:20:19,640
trying to scare you.

381
00:20:19,960 --> 00:20:21,200
I won't get you into trouble.

382
00:20:24,600 --> 00:20:25,400
Move aside.

383
00:20:29,760 --> 00:20:31,880
That medicine isn't for me.

384
00:20:31,880 --> 00:20:33,280
It's for someone
who needs it to stay alive.

385
00:20:37,640 --> 00:20:38,720
Let go of your hand.

386
00:20:44,440 --> 00:20:45,440
Let me help you put it back together.

387
00:20:52,440 --> 00:20:53,840
Is this bracelet

388
00:20:54,880 --> 00:20:56,200
important to you?

389
00:20:58,920 --> 00:21:01,200
You broke my bracelet.

390
00:21:01,400 --> 00:21:03,400
It can't be fixed anymore.

391
00:21:03,480 --> 00:21:04,600
You're annoying,

392
00:21:04,600 --> 00:21:06,200
and so is your mom.

393
00:21:06,200 --> 00:21:08,200
Leave my house.

394
00:21:08,200 --> 00:21:09,200
It's my house.

395
00:21:09,440 --> 00:21:11,200
You're annoying. Go away!

396
00:21:11,480 --> 00:21:15,160
Go!

397
00:21:15,640 --> 00:21:16,440
Yunzheng.

398
00:21:16,640 --> 00:21:17,440
Let go.

399
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:18,720
What are you doing?

400
00:21:20,840 --> 00:21:21,640
Honey.

401
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:23,200
It's all Yuncheng's fault.

402
00:21:23,360 --> 00:21:24,640
Don't blame Yunzheng.

403
00:21:24,960 --> 00:21:26,480
Yuncheng, apologize to your brother.

404
00:21:28,520 --> 00:21:29,440
Yuncheng.

405
00:21:43,200 --> 00:21:44,200
Try to put it together on this paper.

406
00:21:45,200 --> 00:21:46,640
It will be clearer this way.

407
00:22:01,760 --> 00:22:02,960
We can't do it like this.

408
00:22:04,000 --> 00:22:05,400
The letters are in the wrong order.

409
00:22:05,880 --> 00:22:07,600
I've tried many combinations

410
00:22:08,200 --> 00:22:10,400
but can't get a complete meaning
out of it.

411
00:22:10,840 --> 00:22:11,760
Let me help you.

412
00:22:12,480 --> 00:22:13,640
Okay?

413
00:22:51,200 --> 00:22:52,200
Okay, it's done.

414
00:22:53,000 --> 00:22:54,360
Dark rainbow.

415
00:22:55,160 --> 00:22:56,600
That's what

416
00:22:56,600 --> 00:22:58,200
it means in French.

417
00:22:59,480 --> 00:23:00,760
Dark rainbow.

418
00:23:01,600 --> 00:23:02,200
Yeah.

419
00:23:03,120 --> 00:23:04,440
Dark rainbow.

420
00:23:04,440 --> 00:23:06,200
It's a rainbow in the night sky.

421
00:23:06,680 --> 00:23:08,480
It's a super miracle.

422
00:23:12,200 --> 00:23:14,200
The person who gave you this bracelet

423
00:23:15,040 --> 00:23:17,040
probably wanted to bring you good luck.

424
00:23:25,880 --> 00:23:27,200
Is it

425
00:23:28,720 --> 00:23:30,440
from your first love?

426
00:23:34,680 --> 00:23:36,560
Or from your girlfriend?

427
00:23:40,520 --> 00:23:41,600
No.

428
00:23:52,200 --> 00:23:53,200
I've figured it out for you.

429
00:23:53,920 --> 00:23:55,600
You should be feeling better now, right?

430
00:23:57,520 --> 00:23:58,880
You won't report me, will you?

431
00:23:59,840 --> 00:24:01,280
It's another kettle of fish.

432
00:24:21,200 --> 00:24:23,200
I know a lot of rumors

433
00:24:23,200 --> 00:24:25,720
about the dark rainbow.

434
00:24:26,440 --> 00:24:27,200
Would you like to hear them?

435
00:24:31,360 --> 00:24:32,200
Like what?

436
00:24:33,880 --> 00:24:35,200
Like...

437
00:24:36,760 --> 00:24:38,680
Like the fact that the dark rainbow

438
00:24:39,000 --> 00:24:40,600
only appears under specific conditions.

439
00:24:42,880 --> 00:24:44,200
If you're

440
00:24:45,680 --> 00:24:47,000
lucky enough

441
00:24:47,240 --> 00:24:48,200
to see it,

442
00:24:48,520 --> 00:24:49,920
it means

443
00:24:52,680 --> 00:24:54,440
that somewhere in this world,

444
00:24:54,560 --> 00:24:55,400
a miracle

445
00:24:58,200 --> 00:24:59,200
is happening.

446
00:25:00,600 --> 00:25:02,200
It's so romantic, right?

447
00:25:09,920 --> 00:25:11,280
And I also know

448
00:25:11,280 --> 00:25:13,200
where you can see it.

449
00:25:14,960 --> 00:25:15,680
Do you?

450
00:25:15,680 --> 00:25:16,200
Yes.

451
00:25:16,840 --> 00:25:17,840
It's far away.

452
00:25:18,680 --> 00:25:19,680
But it doesn't matter.

453
00:25:19,960 --> 00:25:21,440
As long as you take my car.

454
00:25:21,880 --> 00:25:24,440
For the sake of our friendship tonight.

455
00:25:26,520 --> 00:25:27,200
Give you a 20% discount.

456
00:25:28,160 --> 00:25:28,880
How about that?

457
00:25:30,480 --> 00:25:31,960
No, thanks.

458
00:26:01,640 --> 00:26:02,880
Why don't you push me away?

459
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:04,520
You're too heavy. I can't move.

460
00:26:04,640 --> 00:26:06,200
You could have woken me up.

461
00:26:06,600 --> 00:26:07,640
You've been pressing on me all night.

462
00:26:08,480 --> 00:26:10,160
I fell asleep at dawn.

463
00:26:10,520 --> 00:26:11,200
I just woke up.

464
00:26:12,000 --> 00:26:13,600
How could I have been pressing
on you all night?

465
00:26:13,600 --> 00:26:14,520
I'm not a mountain.

466
00:26:20,200 --> 00:26:21,520
Are you sure you just woke up?

467
00:26:25,480 --> 00:26:27,840
(How can you be so tidy
when you've just woken up?)

468
00:26:27,960 --> 00:26:29,280
(You're so fresh and clean.)

469
00:26:29,840 --> 00:26:30,840
(Suspicious.)

470
00:26:33,840 --> 00:26:35,040
(He's)

471
00:26:35,760 --> 00:26:37,240
(good-looking.)

472
00:26:41,280 --> 00:26:42,520
Who is it for?

473
00:26:47,880 --> 00:26:50,640
You said that medicine is
for extending someone's life.

474
00:26:56,440 --> 00:26:57,680
For someone

475
00:26:58,040 --> 00:26:59,880
who can't come to the hospital.

476
00:27:00,480 --> 00:27:02,200
Why can't he come to the hospital?

477
00:27:05,680 --> 00:27:07,040
Not everyone is like you

478
00:27:07,040 --> 00:27:08,520
in this world,

479
00:27:08,840 --> 00:27:09,920
with a stable income

480
00:27:10,280 --> 00:27:11,200
and good health.

481
00:27:14,600 --> 00:27:17,200
Many people can't afford
to come to the hospital.

482
00:27:20,040 --> 00:27:21,040
What's worse,

483
00:27:22,880 --> 00:27:24,240
even if they have money,

484
00:27:25,920 --> 00:27:27,600
Some diseases can't be cured.

485
00:27:36,440 --> 00:27:37,600
Dr. Gu.

486
00:27:39,680 --> 00:27:43,720
We were here last night, and...

487
00:27:47,200 --> 00:27:49,240
I understand.

488
00:27:50,200 --> 00:27:51,400
She said she Understood.

489
00:27:52,680 --> 00:27:53,680
Understood?

490
00:27:54,760 --> 00:27:56,600
I'm not finished yet.

491
00:27:57,360 --> 00:27:59,440
Don't worry, I didn't see anything.

492
00:28:12,680 --> 00:28:13,680
Come with me.

493
00:28:28,880 --> 00:28:29,880
Last night...

494
00:28:30,680 --> 00:28:31,440
Thank you

495
00:28:32,040 --> 00:28:33,440
for helping me figure out the meaning

496
00:28:33,960 --> 00:28:35,200
behind those letters.

497
00:28:37,000 --> 00:28:38,400
I should be thanking you

498
00:28:38,880 --> 00:28:39,960
for not reporting me.

499
00:28:46,440 --> 00:28:47,200
You can't

500
00:28:48,240 --> 00:28:49,200
take these medicine away.

501
00:28:50,040 --> 00:28:50,840
Please.

502
00:28:51,680 --> 00:28:52,960
I offer you more money, okay?

503
00:28:53,240 --> 00:28:54,680
Double the amount?

504
00:28:55,880 --> 00:28:56,480
No need.

505
00:28:59,760 --> 00:29:01,320
You're so willing to spend money

506
00:29:01,520 --> 00:29:02,720
like a money tree.

507
00:29:03,400 --> 00:29:05,200
This person must be
very important to you.

508
00:29:08,440 --> 00:29:09,520
How about this?

509
00:29:09,920 --> 00:29:12,440
Can you give me a box first?

510
00:29:14,480 --> 00:29:15,200
No, I can't.

511
00:29:32,960 --> 00:29:33,760
Let me keep

512
00:29:34,240 --> 00:29:35,200
these medicine for now.

513
00:29:36,200 --> 00:29:38,840
Bring the patient to the hospital
within 24 hours.

514
00:29:39,200 --> 00:29:40,280
No matter how difficult it is,

515
00:29:40,280 --> 00:29:42,200
we can work it out together.

516
00:29:42,680 --> 00:29:43,880
But you can't

517
00:29:45,440 --> 00:29:47,200
take these prescription drugs so easily.

518
00:29:57,520 --> 00:30:02,000
Shut up, you're making a lot of noise.

519
00:30:02,280 --> 00:30:04,840
Your crying is giving me a headache.
Bear it.

520
00:30:04,960 --> 00:30:06,360
Sakun, come on, get up.

521
00:30:08,440 --> 00:30:09,160
How are you feeling?

522
00:30:09,440 --> 00:30:10,280
I'm getting a headache.

523
00:30:10,400 --> 00:30:11,600
Headache?

524
00:30:12,200 --> 00:30:13,480
How dare you come back?

525
00:30:14,280 --> 00:30:16,040
My house was destroyed because of you.

526
00:30:16,080 --> 00:30:18,880
You have to pay me double.

527
00:30:20,120 --> 00:30:21,040
I'll pay.

528
00:30:21,240 --> 00:30:22,960
But you have to take him
to the hospital.

529
00:30:23,040 --> 00:30:24,880
He can't stop taking his medicine,
don't you know that?

530
00:30:24,960 --> 00:30:25,920
Are you kidding me?

531
00:30:25,960 --> 00:30:28,200
We're poor, don't you know that?

532
00:30:28,200 --> 00:30:29,160
We don't even have enough money to eat.

533
00:30:29,160 --> 00:30:30,320
It's even more impossible
to get medicine.

534
00:30:32,120 --> 00:30:32,960
Sakun.

535
00:30:33,400 --> 00:30:37,160
You wretched child,
why don't you just die?

536
00:30:37,160 --> 00:30:39,480
You're a waste of food.

537
00:30:39,480 --> 00:30:40,320
Sakun.

538
00:30:40,720 --> 00:30:41,920
Do you feel any discomfort anywhere?

539
00:30:41,960 --> 00:30:42,760
Headache.

540
00:30:45,360 --> 00:30:46,160
Oh no.

541
00:30:47,200 --> 00:30:47,960
Let's go.

542
00:30:49,440 --> 00:30:50,720
Put him down.

543
00:30:50,720 --> 00:30:51,480
He needs to go to the hospital
right away.

544
00:30:51,480 --> 00:30:52,600
Otherwise, his life will be in danger.

545
00:30:52,600 --> 00:30:54,000
You caused my house to be destroyed.

546
00:30:54,000 --> 00:30:55,640
Even triple the rent won't be enough
to compensate me.

547
00:30:55,640 --> 00:30:56,160
Money!

548
00:30:56,160 --> 00:30:57,120
You only care about money.

549
00:31:09,220 --> 00:31:10,020
Hello?

550
00:31:10,760 --> 00:31:13,560
You said if I tell you
where Su Wei'an is,

551
00:31:13,560 --> 00:31:14,920
you'll give me money?

552
00:31:15,040 --> 00:31:17,040
She went to the hospital.

553
00:31:20,980 --> 00:31:23,420
[Friendship Hospital]

554
00:31:24,640 --> 00:31:25,960
Dr. Gu, help him!

555
00:31:27,040 --> 00:31:27,640
What happened?

556
00:31:27,960 --> 00:31:28,720
The patient has a headache,

557
00:31:28,720 --> 00:31:29,640
with projectile vomiting

558
00:31:29,640 --> 00:31:30,200
and unsteady gait.

559
00:31:31,260 --> 00:31:32,030
Fang Mingfan.

560
00:31:32,240 --> 00:31:33,640
Take him for a CT scan
of his head immediately.

561
00:31:33,800 --> 00:31:34,200
Hurry up!

562
00:31:34,440 --> 00:31:34,800
Okay.

563
00:31:35,400 --> 00:31:35,960
Be careful.

564
00:31:40,960 --> 00:31:42,960
You're the surgeon
with a zero mortality rate.

565
00:31:43,400 --> 00:31:44,360
Will he be okay?

566
00:31:44,400 --> 00:31:45,400
Don't worry.

567
00:31:45,960 --> 00:31:47,120
Where are his parents?

568
00:31:47,480 --> 00:31:48,640
He might need immediate surgery.

569
00:31:48,800 --> 00:31:49,720
I'll sign it.

570
00:31:49,960 --> 00:31:50,960
You?

571
00:31:51,200 --> 00:31:52,280
Surgery fees and hospitalization fees.

